cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL

This paper deals with the classification of marine mammal vocalizations using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and a novel acoustic representation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of CNNs for classification suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the proposed acoustic representation involves the use of Short-time Fourier Transform (STFT) parameters, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing).
